 
Wear Your C.U.P. Act
Mayoral Legislation of Los Santos

Proposal: 

This legislation will inform the public of the guidelines for protective apparel and allow citizens to have an example of what is and is not protective apparel. These listed examples below are not specific and restrictive rules, but rather allow citizens their freedom of expression of clothing while continuing to protect themselves while performing state jobs around San Andreas. C.U.P. stands for Certified Uniforms of Protection.

Guidelines:

Article 1: Proper Protection Equipment
1.	Electrician
○	Gloves
○	High Visibility Vest
○	Protective Eyewear
2.	Garbage
○	High Visibility Vest
○	Sanitary Gloves
3.	Go Postal
○	Minimum of one piece of Go Postal clothing
4.	Hunter
○	High Visibility Vest
5.	Lumberjack
○	High Visibility Vest
○	Protective Eyewear 
6.	Mining
○	Boots
○	Gloves
○	Protective Eyewear
7.	Plumber
○	Protective Eyewear
○	Sanitary Gloves
8.	Salvage
○	Boots
○	Gloves

Conclusion:

The Mayor’s Office submits this legislation to remove the injunction of the PPE citation by giving the citizens guidelines on proper protective apparel.

Council Votes
Council Member #1 - Approve/Deny
Council Member #2 - Approve/Deny
Council Member #3 - Approve/Deny
